    "Performance analysis on implemented AH-CNN-LSTM-based human motion intention prediction model over traditional heuristic and prediction techniques.",
    "Clinical relevance:The developed human motion intention prediction process is clinically relevant because it enables the implementation of assistive models that can anticipate an individual's movements, resulting in highly responsive and natural support, most importantly for persons with neurological impairments and disabilities, allowing them to do the daily activities with high safety and independence."
